* She�d broken his wing, the roar coming from him was a good sign.
His mind was a cloud of rage and pain, but the man she knew was somewhere in 
that mix of it all, she just had to try and find him.
< Prowl, where are you?> she thought to herself before her mind went blank 
in shok while she saw him lung at her from the corner of her eye.
She was even more surprised, though, when a huge hand suddenly came into the 
picture and lifted him away from her, possibly saving her from the result of 
a broken neck.
For some stupid reason she just stood there and watched as a giant bot 
picked Prowl from her, him struggling in the things grasp.
Where did this come from? It totally snuck up on her, even though she had to 
admit that it was pretty easy since she was dwelling on the fight and not 
too much on things going on around her.  By now the big bot had lifted Prowl 
high in the air and Iron Raptor suddenly realized that if it let go of him 
now and with his broken wing, Prowl would fall to earth and would probably 
make a sickening sound when he landed. She made a sick face at the thought.
< Great job, dumb ass.> her mind teased.
But she suddenly hissed through her teeth when she saw the other hand whoosh 
down towards her now, scrambling to try and get out of the way on all fours. 
But she made a slight gaging sound when the hand caught her tail instead and 
she was suddenly hauled up through the air up-side down!*
